# Add a book to the bookshelf

## Scope (credit-efficient)

- Read **`_data/books/book-schema.json`** once per task — it is the source of truth for required fields, enums, and types (also wired in `.vscode/settings.json` for editor validation).
- Edit **one** list file: `_data/books/[YEAR]bookList.json`. Default to the **newest year** file (e.g. `2026bookList.json`) unless the user names a year.
- **Append** one object before the closing `]`; match **field order and style** of the last entry in that file.
- Every new entry must **conform to the schema** (required keys present; `status`, `type`, and each `tags` item use schema `enum` values only).
- Do **not** search the codebase, scan other year files for duplicates, run `npm`, or commit unless the user asks.

## Schema (from `book-schema.json`)

**Required:** `cover`, `coverAlt`, `link`, `title`, `author`, `tags`, `status`

**Also include:** `subTitle` (`""` if none), `type`, `description` (`""` unless the user provides notes)

| Field | Schema constraint |
|-------|-------------------|
| `cover`, `link` | URI strings |
| `type` | `""`, `book`, `audiobook`, or `ebook` |
| `status` | `want-to-read`, `currently-reading`, `read`, or `dnf` |
| `tags` | Array, min 1; each value from schema `tags.items.enum` |

**Optional (not in schema):** `graphic`, `graphicAlt` — local paths under `/assets/images/`.

**New tag:** If none of the schema tag enums fit, **add the tag to `book-schema.json`** in the same change, then use it in the book entry.

## Lookup

- If the user supplies **link + cover URL**, use them — no web search.
- Only fetch metadata when a required field is missing and the user did not provide it.

## User message shape

```
Title: …
Author: …
Status: want-to-read
Tags: tag1, tag2
Link: …
Cover: … (or "from link")
Notes: … (or none)
```

Batch: numbered lines with the same fields; still one append per book, same file.
